statement.p:
We add two sequences by adding their ith elements:

  (a_i)_{i\in\mathbb{N}}+(b_i)_{i\in\mathbb{N}}
  =(a_i+b_i)_{i\in\mathbb{N}}
.
We scale a sequence by scaling each of its elements:

  k(a_i)_{i\in\mathbb{N}}=(ka_i)_{i\in\mathbb{N}}
.
Then \mathrm{Seq}_{\mathbb{R}} is a vector space.

Let n \geq 0 be an integer and let \mathbb{P}_{n} denote the set of all polynomials with real coefficients of degree at most n \geq 0. Members of \mathbb{P}_{n} have the form
{\pvec}(t) = a_{0} + a_{1}t + a_{2}t^{2} + \cdots + a_{n} t^{n}
where a_{0}, a_{1}, \ldots, a_{n} are real numbers and t is a real variable. The purpose of this activity is to verify that \mathbb{P}_{n} is a vector space.
